Here's the recommended approach using MAUI's lifecycle events and `Preferences`:

**1. In your `App.xaml.cs`, hook the lifecycle events:**

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
    }

    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    {
        var window = new Window(new AppShell());

        window.Deactivated += (s, e) =>
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppBackgroundMessage());

        window.Activated += (s, e) =>
            WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppForegroundMessage());

        return window;
    }
}
```

**2. Define simple message types:**

```csharp
public class AppBackgroundMessage { }
public class AppForegroundMessage { }
```

**3. In your ViewModel, respond to the messages:**

```csharp
public partial class NoteViewModel : ObservableObject, IRecipient<AppBackgroundMessage>,
                                      IRecipient<AppForegroundMessage>
{
    private const string DraftKey = "note_draft";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string draftText = string.Empty;

    public NoteViewModel()
    {
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.RegisterAll(this);
        RestoreDraft(); // also restore on first launch
    }

    public void Receive(AppBackgroundMessage message) => SaveDraft();
    public void Receive(AppForegroundMessage message) => RestoreDraft();

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Default.Set(DraftKey, DraftText);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        DraftText = Preferences.Default.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    // Call this when the user explicitly saves/discards
    public void ClearDraft() => Preferences.Default.Remove(DraftKey);
}
```

**4. Bind in your XAML:**

```xml
<Editor Text="{Binding DraftText}" Placeholder="Start typing..." />
```

**Key points:**

- **`Preferences`** is ideal for small text. For large content, use `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory` and write to a file instead.
- **`WeakReferenceMessenger`** (from `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`) decouples the lifecycle events from your ViewModel.
- **`Window.Deactivated`/`Activated`** fire on all platforms when the app backgrounds/foregrounds.
- Call `ClearDraft()` once the user saves or discards the note to avoid stale restoration.
